            "body": "as far i understand, adding an extmark that inserts virtual text inside a terminal line,\nand neovim’s decoration logic breaks the terminal’s own coloring right?\nif we put guard to prevent, seems solve the issue\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/decoration.c b/src/nvim/decoration.c\nindex 5030c337aa..917d9972bb 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/decoration.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/decoration.c\n@@ -544,6 +544,11 @@ static void decor_range_add_from_inline(DecorState *state, int start_row, int st\n                                         int end_row, int end_col, DecorInline decor, bool owned,\n                                         uint32_t ns, uint32_t mark_id)\n {\n+  // Inline virtual text must not affect terminal buffers\n+  if (state->win && bt_terminal(state->win->w_buffer)) {\n+    return;\n+  }\n+\n   if (decor.ext) {\n     DecorVirtText *vt = decor.data.ext.vt;\n     while (vt) {\n```\n\n<img width=\"381\" height=\"166\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/af7756cb-f3df-4d1a-a2fc-85db9b1033f0\" />",
